===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|雨|云|c1=s|c2=p|t1=rain|t2=cloud|ls=ic|ls2=psc}}. Originally written {{lang|zh|云}}, with the {{lang|zh|雨}} radical added to {{lang|zh|云}} to distinguish from the borrowed sense of “to speak”.

===Etymology===
Very few outside cognates exist. {{zh-ref|Starostin}} compares it with {{cog|lus|vân||sky, the skies, heaven}} and {{cog|mjw|inghun||cloud}}.

Alternatively, this is a derivation from a root meaning “to revolve”. Compare {{och-l|運|gloss=to move}}, {{och-l|回|gloss=to whirl, to circle}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

